	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As some other posts pointed out, using this spell does tend to attract more Undead friends around the area. Having said that, IF your level is fairly high in the zone, this spell is great. Sometimes you end up with a few green-con Undeads running up and attacking you, and you don't want them; they don't give exp and are just waste of time. You've medded to full-mana, and don't want to waste mana either. Then cast this spell! They will go on a merry x-country run, and you stay well clear of the site. Go to near-zone area if necessary. A lot of the time though, they bump into someone meding. Monsters love surprising people who are cosy and meding along the side :) So whoever was meding now has to deal with those low level monsters. To make this process more artificial, stay behind a pack of people meding. When the Undeads return looking for you, they will have to go through the bunch of people siting, and they are likely to drop you as a target in favour of those meding. Doing this isn't very clerical :) But it works. Besides, hey, that person could get exp from them when you wouldn't!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
